The paper deals with secure coding for distributed matrix computation, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a master server and multiple workers suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses trade-offs between recovery threshold and communication load, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
